22#include <sys/cdefs.h>
23#ifndef lint
24__RCSID("$NetBSD: print-symantec.c,v 1.6 2017/02/05 04:05:05 spz Exp $");
25#endif
26
27/* \summary: Symantec Enterprise Firewall printer */
28
29#ifdef HAVE_CONFIG_H
30#include "config.h"
31#endif
32
33#include <netdissect-stdinc.h>
34
35#include "netdissect.h"
36#include "extract.h"
37#include "ethertype.h"
38
39#include "ether.h"
40
41struct symantec_header {
42 uint8_t stuff1[6];
43 uint16_t ether_type;
44 uint8_t stuff2[36];
45};
46
47static inline void
48symantec_hdr_print(netdissect_options *ndo, register const u_char *bp, u_int length)
49{
50 register const struct symantec_header *sp;
51 uint16_t etype;
52
53 sp = (const struct symantec_header *)bp;
54
55 etype = EXTRACT_16BITS(&sp->ether_type);
56 if (!ndo->ndo_qflag) {
57 if (etype <= ETHERMTU)
58 ND_PRINT((ndo, "invalid ethertype %u", etype));
59 else
60 ND_PRINT((ndo, "ethertype %s (0x%04x)",
61 tok2str(ethertype_values,"Unknown", etype),
62 etype));
63 } else {
64 if (etype <= ETHERMTU)
65 ND_PRINT((ndo, "invalid ethertype %u", etype));
66 else
67 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%s", tok2str(ethertype_values,"Unknown Ethertype (0x%04x)", etype)));
68 }
69
70 ND_PRINT((ndo, ", length %u: ", length));
71}
72
73/*
74 * This is the top level routine of the printer. 'p' points
75 * to the ether header of the packet, 'h->ts' is the timestamp,
76 * 'h->len' is the length of the packet off the wire, and 'h->caplen'
77 * is the number of bytes actually captured.
78 */
79u_int
80symantec_if_print(netdissect_options *ndo, const struct pcap_pkthdr *h, const u_char *p)
81{
82 u_int length = h->len;
83 u_int caplen = h->caplen;
84 const struct symantec_header *sp;
85 u_short ether_type;
86
87 if (caplen < sizeof (struct symantec_header)) {
88 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[|symantec]"));
89 return caplen;
90 }
91
92 if (ndo->ndo_eflag)
93 symantec_hdr_print(ndo, p, length);
94
95 length -= sizeof (struct symantec_header);
96 caplen -= sizeof (struct symantec_header);
97 sp = (const struct symantec_header *)p;
98 p += sizeof (struct symantec_header);
99
100 ether_type = EXTRACT_16BITS(&sp->ether_type);
101
102 if (ether_type <= ETHERMTU) {
103 /* ether_type not known, print raw packet */
104 if (!ndo->ndo_eflag)
105 symantec_hdr_print(ndo, (const u_char *)sp, length + sizeof (struct symantec_header));
106
107 if (!ndo->ndo_suppress_default_print)
108 ND_DEFAULTPRINT(p, caplen);
109 } else if (ethertype_print(ndo, ether_type, p, length, caplen, NULL, NULL) == 0) {
110 /* ether_type not known, print raw packet */
111 if (!ndo->ndo_eflag)
112 symantec_hdr_print(ndo, (const u_char *)sp, length + sizeof (struct symantec_header));
113
114 if (!ndo->ndo_suppress_default_print)
115 ND_DEFAULTPRINT(p, caplen);
116 }
117
118 return (sizeof (struct symantec_header));
119}
